<body>
  <h1>VWL</h1>
  <table>
    <tr>
      <th class="white">1. Needs and Types of Goods</th>
      <th class="red">2. Objectives of Economic and Social Policy</th>
      <th class="blue">5. Economic Circulation, Growth, Structural Change</th>
      <th class="yellow">6. Market Economy</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="white">
        <b>Need:</b> Arises from a shortage and desire to eliminate it.<br><br>
        <b>Maslow's Hierarchy:</b> Basic → Safety → Social → Esteem → Self-actualisation<br><br>
        <b>Types of Needs:</b><br>
        - Basic vs. Choice<br>
        - Individual/Collective<br>
        - Tangible/Intangible<br><br>
        <b>Types of Goods:</b><br>
        - Private/Public<br>
        - Economic/Free<br>
        - Investment/Consumption<br><br>
        <b>Economic Principles:</b><br>
        - Maximum: max output from fixed input<br>
        - Minimum: min input for fixed output<br>
        - Optimum: best input-output ratio
      </td>
      <td class="red">
        <b>Magic Polygon Objectives:</b><br>
        - Full employment (2–3% unemployment)<br>
        - Social balance<br>
        - Economic growth<br>
        - Price stability<br>
        - Environmental quality<br>
        - Foreign trade balance<br>
        - Balanced government budget<br><br>
        <b>Objective Relationships:</b><br>
        - Conflict: Price stability ↔ Full employment<br>
        - Harmony: Economic growth ↔ Full employment<br>
        - Neutrality: Price stability ↔ Environmental quality
      </td>
      <td class="blue">
        <b>Simple Economic Circulation:</b> Households ↔ Firms (goods for money)<br><br>
        <b>GDP:</b> Value of all goods/services produced<br>
        <b>National Income (NI):</b> All income earned<br><br>
        <b>Expanded Circulation:</b> Adds government, banks, foreign<br><br>
        <b>Production Factors:</b> Labour, Land, Capital<br>
        <b>Optimal Allocation:</b> Efficient resource use<br><br>
        <b>Labour Productivity:</b><br>
        - Formula: Output ÷ Hours<br>
        - Influenced by tech, knowhow, capital<br><br>
        <b>GDP, GNI, NI:</b><br>
        - GDP: Inside borders<br>
        - GNI: Includes foreign income<br>
        - NI: Earned incomes total<br><br>
        <b>GDP Calculation:</b><br>
        - Production: Output - preperformance + subsidies<br>
        - Usage: C + G + I + (X–M)<br>
        - Income: Salaries + profits + depreciation + taxes – subsidies<br><br>
        <b>Nominal vs. Real GDP:</b><br>
        - Nominal: includes inflation<br>
        - Real: excludes inflation<br><br>
        <b>Applications of GDP:</b><br>
        - Measure growth<br>
        - Compare countries<br>
        - Employment planning<br><br>
        <b>Criticism of GDP:</b><br>
        - Includes negatives (e.g. war)<br>
        - Excludes unpaid work<br>
        - Wealth ≠ Welfare
      </td>
      <td class="yellow">
        <b>Market Forms:</b><br>
        <table style="border: 2px solid black; border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; color: black; text-align: left; table-layout: fixed;">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Market Form</th>
              <th style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Supply Side</th>
              <th style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Example</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Monopoly</td>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">One supplier</td>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Swiss Post (letter)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Oligopoly</td>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Few suppliers</td>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Car market, F&amp;B wholesalers</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Polypol (Free competition)</td>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Many suppliers</td>
              <td style="border: 2px solid black; padding: 8px;">Retail markets</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table><br>
        <b>Preconditions for Polypol:</b><br>
        - Homogeneous goods<br>
        - Market transparency<br>
        - Free entry/exit<br>
        - Rational actors<br><br>

        <b>Price Making:</b><br>
        - Information function<br>
        - Coordination function<br>
        - Guiding function<br><br>

        <b>Supply and Demand Curves:</b><br>
        - Supply: Upward slope<br>
        - Demand: Downward slope<br><br>

        <b>Price Change Effects:</b><br>
        - Price ↑ → Supply ↑, Demand ↓<br>
        - Price ↓ → Supply ↓, Demand ↑<br><br>

        <b>Market Equilibrium:</b><br>
        - Where supply = demand (P*, V*)<br><br>

        <b>Curve Shifts:</b><br>
        - Supply shift: Cost change<br>
        - Demand shift: Income/substitute changes<br><br>

        <b>Price Elasticity:</b><br>
        - Formula: PE = ΔQ% ÷ ΔP%
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</body>
